Description: A rectangular fragment, with one angle broken away, of double-sided thin flake-implement of pale brown flint, with the edges retouched to form a scraper.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, From the surface around the "Qasr"
Curator's comments: One of the three flint "struck flakes" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 74 § 70; see also London, BM, EA 23642 and Boston, MFA, RES.87.111 (deaccessioned)
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 74 § 70)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.78, p.185, pl.27)
